I was wondering if any gnome/halfling rogues could help me.  I have a level 40 gnome rogue on RZ and only now have I started getting more involved in PvP... in the past I've always tried to avoid it.  Problem is my resists are abymsal.  But I'm a gnome rogue!  If I focus on resists, my strength and AC will suffer incredibly and already I seem not up-to-par with other rogues who are lower level than me.  I remember seeing someone say that around level 37 or so he could backstab for about 160ish.. my best backstab with a slimecoated harpoon now is around 180ish.  I feel kind of outdated by all the damage everyone else is doing.  But anyway, how does a gnome rogue maintain his AC, STR, *and* MR? (my STA is pretty low too)<br>
<br>
...and is part of the solution to get Sentry nodrop armor?<br>
<br>
My poison skills are also abysmal.. I have about 90 skill points to waste, but I think I should save them for tinkering.  Are there any guides to increasing this skill quickly?  I already have a good enough pottery skill for pottery, but everything else seems difficult to obtain or way too expensive (I'm poor!).<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 1:25:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gnome Rogue PvP, need advice</span><hr size=1> First question is why you chose Ralos is you tried to avoid pvp?  Not a cut on you, I'm just curious.<br>
<br>
Regarding the other questions:<br>
<br>
1) If you want to survive you'll need to beef up your resists, especially magic and fire.  Yep, it's gonna compromise some of your other stats, but you'll need to do it if you want to hang.  My main pvp rogue is a barbarian so I never had to worry about compromising str for resists.<br>
<br>
2) Poison is a must for any good pvp rogue.  Lookup the poison guide here on the Safehouse to figure out your strategy for raising the skill. <p><FONT SIZE=2 FACE=Dauphin>The more you leave dead, the less you need to watch your back.</FONT><BR><BR><FACE=TIMES>Morvran McGuinness [Shanks], VZ<BR>Smelvin [Da Bashin' Iggles], SZ</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aanladil>Aanladil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 1:44:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RZ</span><hr size=1> The reason why I'm on RZ is because I've always been on RZ.  My best friend introduced me to EQ on RZ and since then I've been there for years.  And I keep hearing how boring it is on blue servers, so I generally avoid it-- it's good in that RZ is always the least populated, and thus the least crowded.  And it does get exciting.  Needing NO DROP and resist gear adds a whole new dimension to the game-- whereas in blue servers you only need to worry about PvE, on red servers you need to be readily aware all the time, and that adds to the excitement and reality of the game.<br>
<br>
I shouldn't say I avoided pvp, it's just that I rarely got into any pvp encounters where I really tried (I always had an inferiority complex-- it was always, &quot;someone's attacking me, there's no way I'll win, how do I get away?&quot; or &quot;oh, I'm going to die, let me poke him.  I'm not going to bag my stuff though.  I'll just keep poking him while I die.&quot;)<br>
<br>
hehe, pitiful <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But I'm more comfortable now as a rogue and I feel I can handle myself in a pvp situation when the odds aren't completely against me.  But I have very little experience, and learning more about pvp is making me worry about my inferior pvp equipment.  MR and nodrop is necessary for pvp-- but so is STR and AC-- without that as a gnome I'm encumbered, out of stamina, and an utter weakling capable only of make 30 pt backstabs and missing all the time, while they cut through me like butter.<br>
<br>
Why am I a gnome?  I dunno, I've always liked gnomes.  And I think I can use my size to my advantage.  But with barbs having 150+ str, and me having only 105 str WITH my gear on (not even sacrificing stuff for resists), I feel pitiful.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 5:54:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RZ</span><hr size=1> Figure that was the case.  Nothing wrong with that reason.<br>
<br>
My advice?  Don't get caught up in the bigger is better stuff.  It used to make me SO jealous when I used to play Mordier on Bertox when rogues my level backstabbed for more damage than I did.  It seemed everyone could hit harder...but that's not the case.<br>
<br>
The damage difference between you and most other rogues is not big...it actually won't differ much at all.  And like you said, your size is a huge advantage (coming from a Barbarian rogue so trust me), so use it.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, it doesn't matter if you can punch your dagger through his whole body...it only has to reach the heart. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aanladil>Aanladil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 11:02:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I see</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the encouragement <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Made some poisons today... was so proud of having an almost full bag of minor poisons... but now I don't want to use them because of all the effort it took. lol<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthisle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thisle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 11:27:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I see</span><hr size=1> All you need for pvp is a 33 skill in poison making...  Run to WK and make spine breaks... i just buy 40 of all the components and make them when i need to...<br>
<br>
For resists, get 7mr bracers (cheap), 9mr/10mr neck (cheap)<br>
14mr rings...bloodstained mantle....earing of essence...illusion mask...rygorr pants/arms or i have Mithril...blackened alloy crown/froggy crown.<br>
<br>
Thats pretty much it.  All those togather probly cost around 5k.  The 14mr rings/froggy crown are pretty expensive...the rest is just really cheap <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Good luck.  And yes im a gnome rogue, my pve str is only 130 somthing, but when i pvp it goes down to 123.  But i have a Bracer of hidden and Goblin earing, so it kinda evens itself out.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthisle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thisle</A> at: 8/16/01 11:27:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aanladil>Aanladil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/17/01 7:03:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks :)</span><hr size=1> Thanks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm really poor, and I hate looting... I'll try to get that cheap stuff though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I already have the 7MR bracers, the mask, and bs mantle.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxezzt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xezzt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/01 5:08:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks :)</span><hr size=1> Look me up on RZ, I think I can help you out some.<br>
<br>
<br>
--Xezzt <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaaryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaaryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/3/01 2:31:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gnome Rogue PvP, need advice</span><hr size=1> Fear not brother, for you have made the correct choice!  The gnome is the best rogue pvper because of their small frame (halflings are small but too ugly to consider).  Who cares about a few extra hps of damage from strength modifiers when you can dance all over the place while those stupid dark elf wizards are trying to figure out who the heck is ripping em a new a-hole.<br><br>
<br><br>
I wouldn't worry about str, ac, or sta.  Stamina would be nice but something that isn't easily tackled.  Concentrate on your resists, a non-moving rogue is a dead rogue...doesn't matter what your str, ac, sta is<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>
<br><br>
Luckily, alot of your resist gear is readily attainable at your level.  Get a dwarven tunic (mr/fr/cr) from Crushbone.  Don't kill Crush yourself though as it will hurt your dark elf faction.  Buy or camp the froglok king crown (20 fr/cr)...at 45-50 and with a group of friends, this is an easy camp.  Get a set of 10 fr rings and a set of 10 cr rings (I don't think they cost that much), I'd keep the fire ones on most of the time.  You don't need alot of no drop stuff.  I pvp'd up to 59 using the items I just listed.  There are a few good resist items from Hate (Woven Shadow gloves come to mind) that you might be able to lay your hands on in a few levels (start making friends with some raiding group members now<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>
<br><br>
Figure out a way to camp Cazic for golem wands (steel golem) and instant gate potions (cazic cenobyte).<br><br>
<br><br>
Start thinking about Ragebringer quest now.  How you could possibly accomplish it as soon as you turn 50.  It's a whole different ballgame when that badboy is in your right hand.<br>
<br>
And last but not least, ALWAYS, ALWAYS, ALWAYS have sow potions.  Become friends with a shaman who can make them.  If you have sow, you will either win or get away 95% of the time (assuming your mr is high enough to avoid root/snare).<br>
<br>
Be small and smart, those are most important! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaaryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaaryn</A> at: 9/3/01 2:42:28 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=474.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=467.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=455.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.threadControl?topicID=455.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=455.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=455.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Ro